request.description:
Fetch metadata for a single project by its numeric ID.

### Method

POST /graphql

### Query

{  
project(id: 1) {  
id  
name  
status  
}  
}

### Variables

Not required.

### Authentication

Required: Authorization: Bearer devtoken123

### Response

{  
"data": {  
"project": {  
"id": "1",  
"name": "Apollo",  
"status": "active"  
}  
}  
}

body.raw:
{
  "query": "query($first:Int!, $name:String){ projects(first:$first, nameContains:$name){ totalCount edges { node { id name status } } pageInfo { hasNextPage endCursor } } }",
  "variables": {
    "first": 2,
    "name": "o"
  }
}

request.description:
Fetch a list of projects, with optional filters and cursor-based pagination.

### Method

POST /graphql

### Query

query($first:Int!, $name:String, $after:String){  
projects(first:$first, nameContains:$name, after:$after){  
totalCount  
edges { cursor node { id name status } }  
pageInfo { hasNextPage endCursor }  
}  
}

### Variables

{  
"first": 2,  
"name": "o"  
}

- `first`: number of results to fetch (max 50)

- `name`: optional substring filter on project name

- `after`: optional cursor for pagination


### Authentication

Required: Authorization: Bearer devtoken123

### Response (example)

{  
"data": {  
"projects": {  
"totalCount": 3,  
"edges": \[  
{ "cursor": "cGlkOjI=", "node": { "id": "2", "name": "Zephyr", "status": "active" }},  
{ "cursor": "cGlkOjQ=", "node": { "id": "4", "name": "Orion", "status": "active" }}  
\],  
"pageInfo": {  
"hasNextPage": true,  
"endCursor": "cGlkOjQ="  
}  
}  
}  
}
